erences==\n<references />\n\n{{Saskatchewan rural municipalities navbox\n| ThisRM  = Blucher No. 343 completely surrounds [[Blucher, Saskatchewan|Blucher]]\n| NorthRM = [[Aberdeen No. 373, Saskatchewan|Aberdeen No. 373]]\n| WestRM  = [[Corman Park No. 344, Saskatchewan|Corman Park No. 344]]\n| EastRM  = [[Colonsay No. 342, Saskatchewan|Colonsay No. 342]]\n| SouthRM = [[Lost River No. 313, Saskatchewan|Lost River No. 313]]\n}}\n{{SKDivision11}}\n\n{{coord|52|00|43|N|106|10|06|W|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Rural municipalities in Saskatchewan|B]]\n[[Category:Blucher No. 343, Saskatchewan| ]]\n[[Category:Division No. 11, Saskatchewan]]\n\n\n{{SKDivision11-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name = RM of Blucher\n| official_name = Rural Municipality of Blucher No. 343\n| settlement_type = Rural Municipality\n| pushpin_map = Saskatchewan\n| coordinates = {{coord|52|00|43|N|106|10|06|W}}\n| subdivision_type = Canada\n| subdivision_name = [[Canada]]\n| subdivision_type1 = Province\n| subdivision_name1 = Saskatchewan\n| established_title = Establishment\n| established_date = 1909\n| leader_title = Reeve\n| leader_name = Dan Greschuk\n| area_land_km2 =789.64 \n| population_total = 2,006\n| population_as_of = 2016\n| population_density_km2 = 2.5\n| area_code = 306\n| website = https://www.rm343.com/\n}}\n\n'''Blucher No. 343''' is a [[rural municipality]] in north-central [[Saskatchewan]] on the [[South Saskatchewan River]]. It is located in [[Division No. 11, Saskatchewan|Division No. 11]]. In 1958, the Patience Lake mine was the first potash mine built in Canada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rm343.com/wp442/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/RM-of-Blucher-Official-Community-Plan.pdf|title=RM of Blucher Official Community Plan|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=2017-06-19}}</ref>\n\n== Demographics ==\n{{Canada census|2016_access_date=2017-06-08|2016_land_area=789.64|2016_mean_hh_income=|2016_median_age=40.2|2016_median_age_f=39.5|2016_median_age_m=40.8|2016_pop_